1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:32,001
(Support Admin Watch on www.kissasia.co, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:40,215
[This drama is fictional and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

3
00:00:40,215 --> 00:00:42,533
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

4
00:00:44,972 --> 00:00:47,109
[Episode 2]

5
00:00:52,205 --> 00:00:53,205
Is that my baby?

6
00:00:53,205 --> 00:00:55,172
No, it's my baby.

7
00:00:58,205 --> 00:01:00,172
I suppose the question was unclear.

8
00:01:00,172 --> 00:01:01,338
I'll ask again.

9
00:01:01,338 --> 00:01:03,238
Am I your baby's father?

10
00:01:03,238 --> 00:01:06,672
Well... I don't know why you think that.

11
00:01:06,672 --> 00:01:08,105
But it's not your baby.

12
00:01:08,105 --> 00:01:11,505
So, let's just go our separate ways.

13
00:01:11,505 --> 00:01:13,472
You keep being this flustered.

14
00:01:13,472 --> 00:01:17,272
Given all the circumstances,
I'm certain I'm your baby's father.

15
00:01:17,272 --> 00:01:20,272
So? What are you trying to say?

16
00:01:21,172 --> 00:01:25,472
You mean... you're going
to take responsibility?

17
00:01:30,172 --> 00:01:32,405
I will

18
00:01:32,405 --> 00:01:33,805
take responsibility.

19
00:01:33,805 --> 00:01:35,905
- Pardon?
- Let's...

20
00:01:36,772 --> 00:01:37,805
Let's get married.

21
00:01:37,805 --> 00:01:39,621
What?

22
00:01:39,621 --> 00:01:43,813
[D-Day, Day 7]

23
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:46,213
Let go.

24
00:01:47,405 --> 00:01:48,905
- Let go.
- No, I can't.

25
00:01:48,905 --> 00:01:49,972
Just let go!

26
00:01:49,972 --> 00:01:51,705
Don't let go.

27
00:01:53,138 --> 00:01:54,838
Hey!

28
00:02:14,772 --> 00:02:17,317
It hasn't been long
since I prescribed you medicine,

29
00:02:17,317 --> 00:02:19,005
[Day 5]
but the cycle is fast.

30
00:02:19,005 --> 00:02:20,872
Still having trouble sleeping?

31
00:02:20,872 --> 00:02:22,172
Yeah, sleep has been...

32
00:02:22,172 --> 00:02:23,705
I thought something happened to you!

33
00:02:23,705 --> 00:02:25,905
- What?
- Do you know how many times I called?

34
00:02:25,905 --> 00:02:27,305
You're a light sleeper...

35
00:02:27,305 --> 00:02:28,438
What are you talking about?
I never got any calls...

36
00:02:28,438 --> 00:02:29,472
[Si Hyeong (10)]

37
00:02:29,472 --> 00:02:32,138
I drank too much that day,
so I probably slept well.

38
00:02:32,138 --> 00:02:33,838
Drank too much?

39
00:02:35,138 --> 00:02:38,538
Was there anything else out of the ordinary?

40
00:02:38,538 --> 00:02:40,572
If you mean other things...

41
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:49,605
[Day 3]

42
00:02:51,105 --> 00:02:52,972
Thank you.

43
00:03:01,905 --> 00:03:04,772
Isn't it about time you act your age?

44
00:03:06,972 --> 00:03:09,005
Wow, working for a liquor company
has its perks.

45
00:03:09,005 --> 00:03:11,005
Using market research as an excuse
to frequent places like this.

46
00:03:11,005 --> 00:03:12,805
Take me along more often, okay?

47
00:03:12,805 --> 00:03:14,505
Here to have fun?

48
00:03:30,172 --> 00:03:31,972
What are you doing? Looking for someone?

49
00:03:31,972 --> 00:03:34,205
No, nothing.

50
00:03:34,205 --> 00:03:36,538
Let's go.

51
00:03:36,538 --> 00:03:38,205
Don't lie.

52
00:03:38,205 --> 00:03:41,672
Is he scanning for tall, pretty women
with his handsome looks?

53
00:03:41,672 --> 00:03:42,705
Hurry up.

54
00:03:42,705 --> 00:03:45,138
Yeah, I'll go.

55
00:03:45,138 --> 00:03:48,205
[Day 2]

56
00:03:48,205 --> 00:03:49,805
Who is she that you're so eager to find?

57
00:03:49,805 --> 00:03:53,805
You must've had some info,
either about her company or her name.

58
00:03:57,605 --> 00:03:59,138
Are you even listening to me?

59
00:03:59,138 --> 00:04:00,505
- Huh?
- Is there any reason

60
00:04:00,505 --> 00:04:03,572
you absolutely have to find her again?

61
00:04:03,572 --> 00:04:05,672
Like, you fell in love at first sight?

62
00:04:05,672 --> 00:04:07,105
Me? Kang Du Jun?

63
00:04:07,105 --> 00:04:08,172
Jeez.

64
00:04:08,172 --> 00:04:10,172
I got curious about her
since I slept well without the pills.

65
00:04:10,172 --> 00:04:11,172
And I have something to give back to her.

66
00:04:11,172 --> 00:04:14,205
What nonsense are you
talking about with that weird face?

67
00:04:14,205 --> 00:04:15,572
Weird?

68
00:04:15,572 --> 00:04:17,605
So it isn't... why say that to me?

69
00:04:17,605 --> 00:04:19,705
Wait, you slept well?

70
00:04:19,705 --> 00:04:21,105
With who?

71
00:04:21,105 --> 00:04:22,905
Who was it?

72
00:04:22,905 --> 00:04:25,285
[Day 1]

73
00:04:31,838 --> 00:04:32,972
[Kang Du Jun]
Huh?

74
00:04:32,972 --> 00:04:36,205
What? This is my signature. Why is it here?

75
00:04:36,205 --> 00:04:37,605
Hey! Come out here, please!

76
00:04:37,605 --> 00:04:39,505
How could you do this to me, huh?

77
00:04:39,505 --> 00:04:40,872
What did I do wrong!

78
00:04:40,872 --> 00:04:43,605
- What's wrong with her?
- Why are you doing this to me?

79
00:04:43,605 --> 00:04:45,438
[Kang Du Jun]
I'm sorry.

80
00:04:49,272 --> 00:04:50,738
That check back then?

81
00:04:50,738 --> 00:04:52,972
Wait.

82
00:04:52,972 --> 00:04:54,917
So...

83
00:04:54,917 --> 00:04:57,172
it was all the same woman?

84
00:04:59,845 --> 00:05:02,373
[D-Day]

85
00:05:16,005 --> 00:05:17,272
Uncle!

86
00:05:17,272 --> 00:05:18,972
You startled me.

87
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:24,138
That startled me.

88
00:05:25,672 --> 00:05:27,805
By the way, you must be really busy lately.

89
00:05:27,805 --> 00:05:30,338
Last week, you only wished me
happy birthday, and that was all.

90
00:05:30,338 --> 00:05:32,705
Have I ever forgotten your birthday?

91
00:05:32,705 --> 00:05:33,805
What is this?

92
00:05:33,805 --> 00:05:35,138
Take a look.

93
00:05:35,138 --> 00:05:37,972
Wow, amazing! It's so pretty!

94
00:05:37,972 --> 00:05:39,305
So pretty.

95
00:05:39,305 --> 00:05:41,272
What do you want to eat?
Let's go get something delicious.

96
00:05:41,272 --> 00:05:43,438
Today? I have somewhere to go.

97
00:05:43,438 --> 00:05:44,838
Where?

98
00:05:44,838 --> 00:05:47,205
I'll drive you, then.

99
00:05:47,205 --> 00:05:48,572
Oh...

100
00:05:48,572 --> 00:05:50,272
Why won't you tell me where you're going?

101
00:05:50,272 --> 00:05:51,738
Is it something you can't tell me?

102
00:05:51,738 --> 00:05:54,172
It's not that, but...

103
00:05:54,172 --> 00:05:55,705
You clearly said you'd give me a ride, right?

104
00:05:55,705 --> 00:05:57,072
No backing out now.

105
00:05:57,072 --> 00:05:58,372
Let's go! Honk, honk!

106
00:05:58,372 --> 00:06:01,272
Don't you remember anything
about the baby's father?

107
00:06:03,472 --> 00:06:05,805
Well...

108
00:06:05,805 --> 00:06:07,838
Oh? Manager!

109
00:06:09,372 --> 00:06:11,272
Is she from your company?

110
00:06:21,872 --> 00:06:22,905
Se Hyeon.

111
00:06:22,905 --> 00:06:24,572
- Is this the punk you were talking about?
- What's wrong with you?

112
00:06:24,572 --> 00:06:26,472
- Manager!
- What are you doing?

113
00:06:26,472 --> 00:06:27,972
Do you know what you've done?

114
00:06:27,972 --> 00:06:30,605
Manager, this is my uncle!

115
00:06:32,405 --> 00:06:33,505
Ms. Jang Hui Won.

116
00:06:33,505 --> 00:06:36,605
You left the baby's ultrasound photo.

117
00:06:55,105 --> 00:06:57,672
I'll take responsibility.

118
00:06:57,672 --> 00:06:59,238
- What?
- Let's get married.

119
00:06:59,238 --> 00:07:01,772
What? Doing what?

120
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,872
- What?
- What?

121
00:07:04,872 --> 00:07:07,005
What did I just say?

122
00:07:07,005 --> 00:07:09,838
You said we get married.

123
00:07:10,738 --> 00:07:11,938
Me?

124
00:07:11,938 --> 00:07:13,938
Yes, you did.

125
00:07:13,938 --> 00:07:15,238
That can't be.

126
00:07:15,238 --> 00:07:17,872
You must have misheard.

127
00:07:17,872 --> 00:07:19,572
Conclusion, yes.

128
00:07:19,572 --> 00:07:21,838
'Let's conclude,' something like that, right?

129
00:07:21,838 --> 00:07:24,238
Ha, seriously.

130
00:07:28,472 --> 00:07:30,672
- Uh, what are you...
- Hold on.

131
00:07:30,672 --> 00:07:32,538
I know it's sudden.

132
00:07:32,538 --> 00:07:34,872
Let me give you some time to think.

133
00:07:35,672 --> 00:07:39,172
For now, go home today,
and we'll meet again soon.

134
00:07:48,572 --> 00:07:49,772
What's going on?

135
00:07:49,772 --> 00:07:53,138
It seems like he's the one
who needs more time to think.

136
00:07:54,072 --> 00:07:56,672
Ugh, whatever.

137
00:08:05,905 --> 00:08:09,405
Even taking responsibility
has different scenarios.

138
00:08:18,605 --> 00:08:22,905
Option 1. Don't get married,
and just pay child support.

139
00:08:27,338 --> 00:08:29,338
- What is this?
- 10 billion won.

140
00:08:29,338 --> 00:08:31,005
- 10 billion?
- It's child support.

141
00:08:31,005 --> 00:08:33,805
If needed, I'll add 10 million won monthly.

142
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:37,538
Don't ask to see the kid later
or say anything else.

143
00:08:45,872 --> 00:08:48,972
This ending feels a bit bitter.

144
00:08:48,972 --> 00:08:53,538
Option 2. I raise the baby,
and she pays me compensation.

145
00:08:54,738 --> 00:08:58,372
Can I hold the baby for a moment?

146
00:09:11,638 --> 00:09:13,572
Who do you think I am?
Selling babies for profit?

147
00:09:13,572 --> 00:09:14,605
Forget it!

148
00:09:14,605 --> 00:09:16,738
No, that's not it...

149
00:09:16,738 --> 00:09:18,472
No...

150
00:09:19,938 --> 00:09:22,572
This is even worse.

151
00:09:22,572 --> 00:09:26,172
Option 3. Get married
and raise the child together.

152
00:09:30,438 --> 00:09:32,205
Why aren't they coming out?

153
00:09:37,005 --> 00:09:39,105
What? I can't see anything. Why?

154
00:09:39,105 --> 00:09:41,672
Could this really be my future?

155
00:09:41,672 --> 00:09:43,605
No way!

156
00:09:47,338 --> 00:09:48,538
Sir.

157
00:09:48,538 --> 00:09:49,838
Welcome.

158
00:09:49,838 --> 00:09:52,105
One B-set and a bottle of Try, please.

159
00:09:52,105 --> 00:09:54,972
Alright, B-set. Thank you.

160
00:09:54,972 --> 00:09:58,072
Yeah, this is when I spend money.
If not now, then when?

161
00:09:58,072 --> 00:10:02,038
Guess there was a reason
I've been so on edge.

162
00:10:06,172 --> 00:10:07,905
Thank you.

163
00:10:19,038 --> 00:10:21,405
Wait... can I not drink anymore?

164
00:10:21,405 --> 00:10:23,141
- Exams are over!
- Over!

165
00:10:23,141 --> 00:10:24,738
[7 Years Ago]
Let's go all out today!

166
00:10:24,738 --> 00:10:27,972
- Our friendship!
- Forever!

167
00:10:35,005 --> 00:10:36,438
Should we really go home?

168
00:10:36,438 --> 00:10:37,638
Ah, wait.

169
00:10:37,638 --> 00:10:41,272
I don't want to go home.
Let's have just one more drink.

170
00:10:41,272 --> 00:10:43,872
- Just one.
- You already had three bottles.

171
00:10:43,872 --> 00:10:45,038
And I have first period tomorrow...

172
00:10:45,038 --> 00:10:48,005
Oh, what? Mi Ran broke up, remember?

173
00:10:48,005 --> 00:10:50,505
- She broke up!
- One more drink.

174
00:10:50,505 --> 00:10:51,872
- She broke up!
- Down for a convenience store run?

175
00:10:51,872 --> 00:10:52,997
- Let's go!
- Here we go again!

176
00:10:52,997 --> 00:10:54,372
Convenience store? I can't.

177
00:10:54,372 --> 00:10:55,705
Oh, please.

178
00:10:55,705 --> 00:10:57,172
- One more drink!
- One more drink!

179
00:10:57,172 --> 00:10:59,438
Okay, okay.

180
00:10:59,438 --> 00:11:03,205
But you all have to promise
to have strictly one drink each.

181
00:11:03,205 --> 00:11:05,172
- Hurry up.
- Let's go.

182
00:11:05,172 --> 00:11:06,972
[2 Years Ago]
Hello, I'm Manager Jang Hui Won

183
00:11:06,972 --> 00:11:08,438
from New Product Development Team.

184
00:11:08,438 --> 00:11:11,238
[Jang Hui Won, Manager]
What? Jang Hui Won, you got promoted?

185
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:14,972
- I'd really appreciate your support.
- Oh, yes.

186
00:11:14,972 --> 00:11:16,372
She's not just any manager.

187
00:11:16,372 --> 00:11:18,505
She's the youngest-ever manager.

188
00:11:18,505 --> 00:11:20,105
Applause!

189
00:11:20,105 --> 00:11:21,372
What?

190
00:11:21,372 --> 00:11:22,905
So cool.

191
00:11:22,905 --> 00:11:25,372
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

192
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:39,013
No...

193
00:11:39,838 --> 00:11:42,438
I'm screwed.

194
00:11:46,373 --> 00:11:48,138
What's wrong?

195
00:11:49,938 --> 00:11:52,638
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

196
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:55,205
Sir.

197
00:11:55,205 --> 00:11:59,605
I mean, it's just that...

198
00:12:00,338 --> 00:12:04,165
You can't do this to me.

199
00:12:04,165 --> 00:12:05,957
Jeez.

200
00:12:06,805 --> 00:12:08,738
Looks like you had a tough day.

201
00:12:08,738 --> 00:12:11,605
This is the cognac I really treasure.

202
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:14,772
Drink this and shake it off.

203
00:12:21,505 --> 00:12:26,005
Sir, just pretend you're doing this for me.

204
00:12:26,005 --> 00:12:27,805
Instead, can you

205
00:12:27,805 --> 00:12:29,138
drink and wow once?

206
00:12:29,138 --> 00:12:30,872
Me?

207
00:12:33,672 --> 00:12:35,472
Want me to do it?

208
00:12:45,872 --> 00:12:48,138
Being a mom isn't easy, is it?

209
00:12:48,138 --> 00:12:49,605
How did you know?

210
00:12:49,605 --> 00:12:52,338
If you can't drink your favorite alcohol,
it's one of two things.

211
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:55,538
Either you're terminally ill,
or you're pregnant.

212
00:13:08,705 --> 00:13:11,738
I had a child at twenty-two.

213
00:13:11,738 --> 00:13:16,705
Back then, I was overwhelmed,
so I kept the baby without knowing better.

214
00:13:16,705 --> 00:13:20,205
But when I think of everything
I gave up afterward,

215
00:13:20,205 --> 00:13:24,272
- well...
- Did you regret it?

216
00:13:24,272 --> 00:13:26,938
Well, I guess it depends on the person.

217
00:13:26,938 --> 00:13:30,572
But if you're not prepared,
it can be really hard.

218
00:13:30,572 --> 00:13:34,805
Even if the baby is adorable,
the child and my life are on separate paths.

219
00:13:36,238 --> 00:13:38,238
It's complicated.

220
00:13:39,472 --> 00:13:43,372
You seem troubled.
What does the baby's father say?

221
00:13:43,372 --> 00:13:45,072
Well...

222
00:13:46,005 --> 00:13:48,972
Sometimes, talking to
a stranger isn't so bad.

223
00:13:48,972 --> 00:13:51,572
You can open up about things.

224
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:02,838
This baby wasn't planned.

225
00:14:02,838 --> 00:14:04,872
At the most crucial moment,

226
00:14:04,872 --> 00:14:09,505
a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity
has arrived alongside this new life.

227
00:14:10,772 --> 00:14:16,038
It's something I caused,
and I know I have to take responsibility,

228
00:14:17,072 --> 00:14:19,438
but I feel completely lost.

229
00:14:19,438 --> 00:14:21,538
You don't need to feel guilty.

230
00:14:21,538 --> 00:14:26,472
Would a child born out of regret
and unpreparedness really be happy?

231
00:14:28,005 --> 00:14:31,072
If I were you, Hui Won,

232
00:14:31,072 --> 00:14:32,938
I'd chase the opportunity.

233
00:14:32,938 --> 00:14:36,572
Because dreams all have their timing.

234
00:14:43,638 --> 00:14:45,138
Yes.

235
00:14:45,138 --> 00:14:47,172
How about dinner tonight?

236
00:14:47,172 --> 00:14:50,338
Let's have a quick meeting over a meal,

237
00:14:53,905 --> 00:14:56,238
and I'll contact you again.

238
00:14:56,238 --> 00:14:57,972
Okay.

239
00:14:59,372 --> 00:15:02,138
Here are the resume and documents
of Jang Hui Won that you requested.

240
00:15:02,138 --> 00:15:03,872
Good work.

241
00:15:06,757 --> 00:15:08,453
[Jang Hui Won]

242
00:15:09,372 --> 00:15:10,572
[Family Relationship Certificate]

243
00:15:10,572 --> 00:15:12,572
[Jang Hui Won, Manager,
New Product Development Team, Taehan Liquor]

244
00:15:17,372 --> 00:15:20,105
She's pregnant?

245
00:15:21,205 --> 00:15:23,072
Interesting.

246
00:15:40,472 --> 00:15:43,038
[Jang Hui Won]
Did you get home safely?

247
00:15:52,038 --> 00:15:54,605
One, two, three.

248
00:15:59,138 --> 00:16:01,305
- Here.
- Thank you.

249
00:16:03,872 --> 00:16:05,205
Ah, that hits the spot.

250
00:16:05,205 --> 00:16:06,772
- What about you?
- I'm fine.

251
00:16:06,772 --> 00:16:08,205
You drink it.

252
00:16:08,205 --> 00:16:10,672
If you keep giving everything away
like that, you'll be left with nothing.

253
00:16:10,672 --> 00:16:12,672
You're always like this
with your wife too, right?

254
00:16:12,672 --> 00:16:14,738
We're family.

255
00:16:14,738 --> 00:16:17,572
She's the one I should look after the most.

256
00:16:18,205 --> 00:16:19,238
Brother.

257
00:16:19,238 --> 00:16:20,472
What does marriage mean to you?

258
00:16:20,472 --> 00:16:22,105
- That's so random.
- Just asking.

259
00:16:22,105 --> 00:16:24,038
You announced you'd marry
as soon as you started college.

260
00:16:24,038 --> 00:16:27,205
Our parents have such
high expectations of you.

261
00:16:30,238 --> 00:16:32,072
I guess I really needed someone on my side.

262
00:16:32,072 --> 00:16:36,405
People say marriage is the end of your life,

263
00:16:36,405 --> 00:16:39,172
but honestly, I'm loving my life right now.

264
00:16:39,172 --> 00:16:44,338
My wife and Se Hyeon kind of complete
the anxious person I used to be.

265
00:16:44,338 --> 00:16:45,672
Then what about me?

266
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:48,238
I've always been on your side.

267
00:16:48,238 --> 00:16:49,805
Dear Du Jun.

268
00:16:49,805 --> 00:16:50,872
So you felt left out?

269
00:16:50,872 --> 00:16:52,505
Oh, come on, stop treating me like a kid.

270
00:16:52,505 --> 00:16:54,938
Hey, avoiding me? I'm trying
to show you some love.

271
00:16:54,938 --> 00:16:56,272
- No, no!
- Get over here.

272
00:16:56,272 --> 00:16:57,972
- I really hate this!
- Hey!

273
00:16:57,972 --> 00:16:58,972
Come here quick.

274
00:16:58,972 --> 00:17:00,938
You need to be careful.

275
00:17:00,938 --> 00:17:04,172
Watch your step, you'll fall.

276
00:17:42,338 --> 00:17:45,105
Why am I so tired?

277
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:55,205
[Did you get home safely?]

278
00:17:55,205 --> 00:17:58,272
Ugh, don't know. I'm tired.

279
00:18:08,472 --> 00:18:10,138
You don't need to feel guilty.

280
00:18:10,138 --> 00:18:14,005
Would a child born out of regret
and unpreparedness really be happy?

281
00:18:14,005 --> 00:18:17,338
If I were you, Hui Won,
I'd chase the opportunity.

282
00:18:17,338 --> 00:18:20,238
Because dreams all have their timing.

283
00:18:20,238 --> 00:18:21,938
Right.

284
00:18:22,838 --> 00:18:25,505
It took me so much to get this far...

285
00:18:37,272 --> 00:18:42,597
[Study in Germany. This time,
I'm going. No matter what!]

286
00:18:44,905 --> 00:18:47,438
What? Why isn't she reading it?

287
00:18:58,138 --> 00:18:59,705
Did she at least save my number?

288
00:18:59,705 --> 00:19:01,472
[Jang Hui Won]

289
00:19:04,138 --> 00:19:07,405
Uncle! Uncle!

290
00:19:09,238 --> 00:19:10,738
Uncle, are you out of your mind?

291
00:19:10,738 --> 00:19:13,238
It's not just anyone, it's your kid!
And you won't even talk about marriage?

292
00:19:13,238 --> 00:19:15,238
It's not that I won't,
but in a different way...

293
00:19:15,238 --> 00:19:16,372
A different way? Like what?

294
00:19:16,372 --> 00:19:19,838
Paying it off with settlement money,
or child support like that?

295
00:19:19,838 --> 00:19:22,172
Raising a child requires so much care.

296
00:19:22,172 --> 00:19:23,972
You think money solves everything
and you can just walk away?

297
00:19:23,972 --> 00:19:26,138
You're completely selfish and irresponsible.

298
00:19:26,138 --> 00:19:28,138
I'm so disappointed in you, Uncle.

299
00:19:30,338 --> 00:19:32,238
But you're together
because you like each other.

300
00:19:32,238 --> 00:19:34,572
Yet even now, you insist
on staying unmarried?

301
00:19:34,572 --> 00:19:36,305
That's not it...

302
00:19:38,472 --> 00:19:41,405
You won't marry because of me, right?

303
00:19:41,405 --> 00:19:43,438
- Se Hyeon.
- You keep avoiding blind dates,

304
00:19:43,438 --> 00:19:46,138
and refusing to get married.

305
00:19:46,138 --> 00:19:49,238
I feel it's all because of me, and it hurts.

306
00:20:08,872 --> 00:20:09,938
Manager Jang.

307
00:20:09,938 --> 00:20:11,205
Guten Tag.

308
00:20:11,205 --> 00:20:12,838
What, you don't know German?

309
00:20:12,838 --> 00:20:14,138
Morgen!

310
00:20:14,138 --> 00:20:16,357
- Ugh.
- He's just jealous you are going to Germany.

311
00:20:16,357 --> 00:20:18,738
The results haven't even been announced yet.

312
00:20:18,738 --> 00:20:20,572
From last year through this first half,

313
00:20:20,572 --> 00:20:22,538
has anyone performed as well as you?

314
00:20:22,538 --> 00:20:25,705
Seriously, everyone knows
the announcement's coming today.

315
00:20:25,705 --> 00:20:27,338
Please stay calm.

316
00:20:27,338 --> 00:20:28,905
Assistant Manager Choi.

317
00:20:28,905 --> 00:20:30,105
She's saying this out of envy.

318
00:20:30,105 --> 00:20:31,972
From what I see, it seems you are
the most jealous, Manager Nah.

319
00:20:31,972 --> 00:20:33,072
I'm not.

320
00:20:33,072 --> 00:20:34,872
- You're clearly jealous.
- Why would I be jealous?

321
00:20:34,872 --> 00:20:36,738
- It's posted.
- What? Who is it? Me?

322
00:20:36,738 --> 00:20:38,605
- The results are out.
- So who is it?

323
00:20:38,605 --> 00:20:40,305
It's me.

324
00:20:45,638 --> 00:20:47,672
I got selected.

325
00:20:47,672 --> 00:20:48,938
[Final Selectee: Jang Hui Won]
Oh my goodness!

326
00:20:48,938 --> 00:20:52,105
Congratulations, this is wonderful news.

327
00:21:07,238 --> 00:21:08,405
You startled me, seriously.

328
00:21:08,405 --> 00:21:10,372
Make some noise when you come in.
When did you get here?

329
00:21:10,372 --> 00:21:12,005
I've been here since you were a baby.

330
00:21:12,005 --> 00:21:13,738
Hold on.

331
00:21:14,372 --> 00:21:18,072
Now it's not that you applied perfume,
but you practically bathed in it.

332
00:21:18,072 --> 00:21:21,105
Well, as president, I have to maintain
some dignity, you know?

333
00:21:21,105 --> 00:21:23,405
Wasn't today just a preliminary site visit?

334
00:21:23,405 --> 00:21:24,605
Who are you trying to impress?

335
00:21:24,605 --> 00:21:27,738
You're overdoing it. Way too much effort.

336
00:21:30,005 --> 00:21:32,338
You, please put in some effort.

337
00:21:32,338 --> 00:21:34,938
Why aren't you trying?
What are you relying on?

338
00:21:34,938 --> 00:21:36,705
This is ridiculous.

339
00:21:36,705 --> 00:21:39,072
I did put in effort. A lot of it, actually.

340
00:21:39,072 --> 00:21:40,138
Alright.

341
00:21:40,138 --> 00:21:42,838
From this angle, there's no issue here.

342
00:21:42,838 --> 00:21:44,938
But here...

343
00:21:44,938 --> 00:21:46,305
How should I put it... It's weird.

344
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:49,238
And it's strange and kind of bland-looking.

345
00:21:50,149 --> 00:21:52,538
Hey...

346
00:21:52,538 --> 00:21:54,757
What do you mean it's weird!

347
00:21:55,557 --> 00:21:58,341
Jeez.

348
00:21:59,772 --> 00:22:01,538
So what, is it...

349
00:22:01,538 --> 00:22:06,338
'The final touch of fashion
is scent, not the face?'

350
00:22:07,905 --> 00:22:09,638
You little punk.

351
00:22:26,072 --> 00:22:28,172
- Aren't you leaving?
- I am!

352
00:22:28,172 --> 00:22:29,272
Oh no, I got it in my mouth.

353
00:22:29,272 --> 00:22:32,705
Jeez, you are such an annoying type.

354
00:22:35,472 --> 00:22:38,038
By the way, this isn't about me.

355
00:22:38,038 --> 00:22:42,005
But what's the psychology
of people who ignore texts?

356
00:22:42,005 --> 00:22:43,072
It's simple.

357
00:22:43,072 --> 00:22:45,205
First, they hate that sender.

358
00:22:45,205 --> 00:22:47,772
Second, they absolutely despise them.

359
00:22:47,772 --> 00:22:49,005
Third, they're insanely, maddeningly...

360
00:22:49,005 --> 00:22:50,005
Hey, a fly!

361
00:22:50,005 --> 00:22:52,005
- A fly!
- Whoa, hold on, I'm driving!

362
00:22:52,005 --> 00:22:54,172
- There's a fly
- I know, I'm driving!

363
00:22:54,172 --> 00:22:56,672
What? Someone dislikes you?

364
00:22:56,672 --> 00:22:59,705
Have you ever seen anyone who dislikes me?

365
00:22:59,705 --> 00:23:00,738
Oh, whatever.

366
00:23:00,738 --> 00:23:02,138
We'll see who regrets it later.

367
00:23:02,138 --> 00:23:04,172
Wow, Kang Du Jun.

368
00:23:04,172 --> 00:23:06,738
Are you asking me for relationship advice?

369
00:23:08,305 --> 00:23:12,305
My wife and Se Hyeon kind of complete
the anxious person I used to be.

370
00:23:12,305 --> 00:23:14,672
I'll tell you about my love life.

371
00:23:14,672 --> 00:23:16,972
- Back then...
- I've made up my mind.

372
00:23:16,972 --> 00:23:18,372
About what?

373
00:23:18,372 --> 00:23:19,372
I'm going to get married.

374
00:23:19,372 --> 00:23:21,105
Huh?

375
00:23:23,505 --> 00:23:25,672
Hey! Watch the road!

376
00:23:27,172 --> 00:23:28,505
What... get married?

377
00:23:28,505 --> 00:23:30,205
Hey, you said you wouldn't.

378
00:23:30,205 --> 00:23:32,305
- I did.
- And now?

379
00:23:32,305 --> 00:23:33,772
I'm just curious.

380
00:23:33,772 --> 00:23:37,138
Thinking about it, morally
and cost-effectively...

381
00:23:37,138 --> 00:23:38,605
It's better to get it over with quickly.

382
00:23:38,605 --> 00:23:40,805
What nonsense is this? Explain it properly.

383
00:23:40,805 --> 00:23:42,638
Did the chairman say he won't hand over
the company if you don't marry?

384
00:23:42,638 --> 00:23:45,372
Or did your ideal woman suddenly appear?

385
00:23:45,372 --> 00:23:47,938
What on earth are you thinking?

386
00:23:47,938 --> 00:23:50,272
You won't marry because of me, right?

387
00:23:50,272 --> 00:23:52,172
- Se Hyeon.
- You keep avoiding blind dates,

388
00:23:52,172 --> 00:23:54,772
and refusing to get married.

389
00:23:54,772 --> 00:23:58,005
I feel it's all because of me, and it hurts.

390
00:23:58,005 --> 00:23:59,538
What is this even supposed to mean?

391
00:23:59,538 --> 00:24:01,005
You... ah!

392
00:24:01,005 --> 00:24:04,272
Is this some kind of strategic marriage
between companies?

393
00:24:04,272 --> 00:24:05,573
Oh, I don't know.

394
00:24:05,573 --> 00:24:06,638
Wait.

395
00:24:06,638 --> 00:24:07,972
That might actually be better.

396
00:24:07,972 --> 00:24:09,738
- Huh?
- Everyone around us

397
00:24:09,738 --> 00:24:11,705
is in arranged marriages for show.

398
00:24:11,705 --> 00:24:14,472
For us, marriage is just
another business move.

399
00:24:14,472 --> 00:24:16,305
So why not go through with it?

400
00:24:16,305 --> 00:24:20,705
Who knows? Maybe marriage
will fix my current instability.

401
00:24:20,705 --> 00:24:22,938
You're seriously sick.
Let's go to the hospital.

402
00:24:22,938 --> 00:24:24,538
Anyway, that's what you should know.

403
00:24:24,538 --> 00:24:26,305
What, are you getting married by yourself?

404
00:24:26,305 --> 00:24:27,505
Do you even have a bride?

405
00:24:27,505 --> 00:24:29,172
I'm on my way to meet her now.

406
00:24:29,172 --> 00:24:30,938
That bride you're so curious about...

407
00:24:30,938 --> 00:24:32,638
Bride?

408
00:24:35,138 --> 00:24:37,272
Are we going to church now or something?

409
00:24:42,405 --> 00:24:44,438
No responsibility.

410
00:24:44,438 --> 00:24:46,305
Guilty conscience.

411
00:24:46,305 --> 00:24:47,472
A free life.

412
00:24:47,472 --> 00:24:52,238
As you know, when our new president
arrives, he'll tour every floor.

413
00:24:52,238 --> 00:24:54,338
Everyone, please keep things tidy.

414
00:24:54,338 --> 00:24:56,072
- Environmental cleanup...
- Is she in shock from happiness?

415
00:24:56,072 --> 00:24:57,772
She's been waiting for this moment.

416
00:24:57,772 --> 00:24:59,038
Maybe the tension finally melted away.

417
00:24:59,038 --> 00:25:00,038
- Right?
- And one more thing.

418
00:25:00,038 --> 00:25:01,038
Our team's business proposal...

419
00:25:01,038 --> 00:25:03,138
Studying in Germany.

420
00:25:03,138 --> 00:25:04,272
My dream coming true.

421
00:25:04,272 --> 00:25:05,701
Manager Nah, take charge of this
and organize it once.

422
00:25:05,701 --> 00:25:07,205
Assistant Manager Choi, support him.

423
00:25:07,205 --> 00:25:10,638
- Yes.
- And for the remaining staff,

424
00:25:10,638 --> 00:25:12,272
- I was so close.
- you have the performance plan, right?

425
00:25:12,272 --> 00:25:14,905
Organize that and report it to me.

426
00:25:14,905 --> 00:25:16,472
Tak Soo, compile it and report to me.

427
00:25:16,472 --> 00:25:17,805
Understood.

428
00:25:17,805 --> 00:25:18,838
And...

429
00:25:18,838 --> 00:25:20,372
Taking responsibility.

430
00:25:20,372 --> 00:25:23,738
- Single mom, lack of money.
- About the new product proposal.

431
00:25:23,738 --> 00:25:25,005
It was seriously lacking. Check...

432
00:25:25,005 --> 00:25:26,938
Workaholic.

433
00:25:29,305 --> 00:25:31,672
A lonely child.

434
00:25:31,672 --> 00:25:33,772
A bad mother.

435
00:25:33,772 --> 00:25:35,872
Understood.

436
00:25:35,872 --> 00:25:38,138
A bad mother.

437
00:25:39,972 --> 00:25:43,505
- Looks like the meeting prep is mostly done.
- Alright.

438
00:25:43,505 --> 00:25:46,338
He might start next week,

439
00:25:46,338 --> 00:25:48,005
so don't let your schedules get disrupted.

440
00:25:48,005 --> 00:25:53,105
And with Manager Jang leaving
for Germany, there's a lot to wrap up.

441
00:25:53,105 --> 00:25:55,238
[Regular deposit]

442
00:25:55,238 --> 00:25:57,705
This won't even come close to enough.

443
00:26:03,538 --> 00:26:05,238
Manager Jang.

444
00:26:06,372 --> 00:26:08,138
Manager Jang.

445
00:26:09,538 --> 00:26:11,238
Manager Jang!

446
00:26:13,972 --> 00:26:16,005
Are you even listening?

447
00:26:16,005 --> 00:26:17,705
I'm sorry.

448
00:26:30,605 --> 00:26:32,638
Oh, I can't drink this.

449
00:26:34,672 --> 00:26:35,872
Switch with me.

450
00:26:35,872 --> 00:26:38,238
This is warm milk.

451
00:26:44,338 --> 00:26:46,938
Are you my aunt now?

452
00:26:48,325 --> 00:26:49,638
Oh.

453
00:26:49,638 --> 00:26:52,805
I'll keep it a secret at work. Don't worry.

454
00:26:53,438 --> 00:26:55,305
- Um...
- My uncle

455
00:26:55,305 --> 00:26:57,338
is not very skilled at things
outside of work.

456
00:26:57,338 --> 00:26:59,301
Especially, when it comes to dating
and relationships.

457
00:26:59,301 --> 00:27:01,189
He's kind of under-socialized.

458
00:27:01,972 --> 00:27:04,038
Anyway, all that is just

459
00:27:04,038 --> 00:27:07,605
because of his compulsion
to be perfect at everything.

460
00:27:07,605 --> 00:27:10,272
Please look upon him favorably.

461
00:27:10,272 --> 00:27:12,705
He says he won't get married,

462
00:27:12,705 --> 00:27:15,905
and he acts overly conservative
about marriage,

463
00:27:15,905 --> 00:27:18,705
but we all know that's not
how he really feels.

464
00:27:18,705 --> 00:27:21,538
It's all because of me.

465
00:27:24,261 --> 00:27:25,705
Ah.

466
00:27:25,705 --> 00:27:27,938
So you don't know yet.

467
00:27:27,938 --> 00:27:31,172
Anyway, you'll find out gradually.

468
00:27:39,405 --> 00:27:41,338
He says he won't get married,

469
00:27:41,338 --> 00:27:44,138
and he acts overly conservative
about marriage,

470
00:27:44,138 --> 00:27:46,572
but we all know that's not
how he really feels.

471
00:27:46,572 --> 00:27:49,138
It's all because of me.

472
00:27:49,138 --> 00:27:51,472
What's that supposed to mean?

473
00:27:59,538 --> 00:28:01,738
Why is he here?

474
00:28:01,738 --> 00:28:04,405
And I told you,

475
00:28:04,405 --> 00:28:05,872
things like who the CEO is aren't important.

476
00:28:05,872 --> 00:28:09,372
But it's not that he's currently
managing operations,

477
00:28:09,372 --> 00:28:10,372
it's about maintaining relationships.

478
00:28:10,372 --> 00:28:12,638
We need to maintain those connections.

479
00:28:12,638 --> 00:28:14,705
So first impressions

480
00:28:14,705 --> 00:28:16,505
- are extremely important.
- Oh, no.

481
00:28:16,505 --> 00:28:17,938
So in short,

482
00:28:17,938 --> 00:28:19,838
for example, when passing
by employees like this,

483
00:28:19,838 --> 00:28:21,872
you should smile and say hello,

484
00:28:21,872 --> 00:28:23,397
but you don't smile...

485
00:28:23,397 --> 00:28:24,805
Where did he go?

486
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:29,072
Du Jun!

487
00:28:30,938 --> 00:28:32,672
Wait, why...

488
00:28:34,105 --> 00:28:36,005
Are you okay?

489
00:28:36,005 --> 00:28:37,572
Why on earth are you here?

490
00:28:37,572 --> 00:28:40,305
Did you investigate my background?

491
00:28:40,305 --> 00:28:42,638
Did you forget we agreed
to reach a conclusion soon?

492
00:28:42,638 --> 00:28:45,538
So what exactly is that conclusion?

493
00:28:48,438 --> 00:28:50,705
I've decided.

494
00:28:50,705 --> 00:28:52,405
I'll marry you.

495
00:28:52,405 --> 00:28:53,672
What?

496
00:28:53,672 --> 00:28:56,405
Are you going to keep the baby?

497
00:28:59,838 --> 00:29:01,738
Whether you give birth or not is your choice,

498
00:29:01,738 --> 00:29:05,572
but regardless of that, I also
have responsibilities for my child.

499
00:29:05,572 --> 00:29:08,272
So if you're going to keep it, let's hurry.

500
00:29:08,272 --> 00:29:12,205
I'd prefer the wedding be held this year.

501
00:29:12,205 --> 00:29:13,538
Hey.

502
00:29:13,538 --> 00:29:15,738
It's not hey. I'm Kang Du Jun.

503
00:29:15,738 --> 00:29:17,438
Fine, Mr. Kang Du Jun.

504
00:29:17,438 --> 00:29:20,938
Looks like you've been
getting way ahead of yourself,

505
00:29:20,938 --> 00:29:23,805
but I've never once considered marrying you.

506
00:29:23,805 --> 00:29:26,505
My own issues are complicated enough,

507
00:29:26,505 --> 00:29:28,572
so let's just go our separate ways.

508
00:29:28,572 --> 00:29:30,272
Let's pretend

509
00:29:31,205 --> 00:29:33,338
this never happened.

510
00:29:34,338 --> 00:29:37,505
You can't just erase something
that already happened.

511
00:29:37,505 --> 00:29:38,538
What I'm saying is...

512
00:29:38,538 --> 00:29:39,872
What's so special about marriage anyway?

513
00:29:39,872 --> 00:29:42,438
Marriage is business too.

514
00:29:42,438 --> 00:29:45,138
If you really want,
let's write up a contract.

515
00:29:45,138 --> 00:29:48,905
Of course, with the child's care
as the top priority.

516
00:29:49,738 --> 00:29:50,972
What did you say?

517
00:29:50,972 --> 00:29:54,705
Then I definitely can't agree
to a marriage like that.

518
00:29:54,705 --> 00:29:56,338
Why not?

519
00:29:56,338 --> 00:29:58,172
I've already made
future plans for the child...

520
00:29:58,172 --> 00:29:59,705
You booked that place?

521
00:29:59,705 --> 00:30:01,538
Yes, I pulled some strings.

522
00:30:01,538 --> 00:30:03,272
Shh.

523
00:30:35,238 --> 00:30:36,238
What?

524
00:30:36,238 --> 00:30:37,772
Team leader, this place is locked.

525
00:30:37,772 --> 00:30:39,672
But you said you booked it for this time.

526
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:41,972
President.

527
00:30:41,972 --> 00:30:45,805
But we were together. Where did he go?

528
00:30:49,605 --> 00:30:52,272
Is someone inside?

529
00:30:52,272 --> 00:30:55,005
Oh no, what do we do?

530
00:30:55,005 --> 00:30:57,505
It seems locked from the inside.

531
00:31:03,072 --> 00:31:04,672
Then to the manager's office...

532
00:31:04,672 --> 00:31:07,772
What do you mean? We just go out and explain.

533
00:31:07,772 --> 00:31:08,772
No way.

534
00:31:08,772 --> 00:31:12,072
This is the perfect situation
for misunderstandings.

535
00:31:13,338 --> 00:31:15,038
I'll try forcing it open.

536
00:31:15,038 --> 00:31:16,972
What? You're going to force the door open?

537
00:31:16,972 --> 00:31:18,405
Call quickly.

538
00:31:18,405 --> 00:31:20,838
Then try calling me first.

539
00:31:26,305 --> 00:31:28,261
But I don't know your number.

540
00:31:28,261 --> 00:31:29,872
Alright.

541
00:31:29,872 --> 00:31:31,272
I knew it.

542
00:31:31,272 --> 00:31:32,738
Haven't you even saved my number?

543
00:31:32,738 --> 00:31:35,333
That's not important right now.

544
00:31:36,105 --> 00:31:38,205
You don't even read texts
from unknown numbers?

545
00:31:38,205 --> 00:31:40,272
Should I at least be grateful
you didn't block me?

546
00:31:40,272 --> 00:31:42,638
Okay, okay. I'm sorry about that.

547
00:31:42,638 --> 00:31:43,972
We'll really get caught like this.

548
00:31:43,972 --> 00:31:45,638
Do something.

549
00:31:45,638 --> 00:31:47,605
Ah, please.

550
00:31:47,605 --> 00:31:49,305
Three!

551
00:31:51,269 --> 00:31:52,738
Ah.

552
00:31:52,738 --> 00:31:53,905
- Ouch, my nose!
- What the...

553
00:31:53,905 --> 00:31:55,813
What's going on?

554
00:31:55,813 --> 00:31:58,638
President?

555
00:32:00,261 --> 00:32:01,829
Ouch.

556
00:32:04,325 --> 00:32:06,072
Ouch.

557
00:32:06,072 --> 00:32:07,538
Oh, President, I'm so sorry.

558
00:32:07,538 --> 00:32:08,972
I didn't know you were inside.

559
00:32:08,972 --> 00:32:11,805
- President?
- Manager Jang, are you even listening?

560
00:32:11,805 --> 00:32:13,438
I'm sorry.

561
00:32:13,438 --> 00:32:16,838
As you know, when our new president
arrives, he'll tour every floor.

562
00:32:16,838 --> 00:32:18,838
Everyone, please keep things tidy.

563
00:32:18,838 --> 00:32:23,472
He might start next week,
so don't let your schedules get disrupted.

564
00:32:23,472 --> 00:32:25,838
Then that president...

565
00:32:25,838 --> 00:32:27,605
I'm Kang Du Jun.

566
00:32:27,605 --> 00:32:31,272
But why are you here?

567
00:32:31,272 --> 00:32:32,638
And why are you here, Manager Jang?

568
00:32:32,638 --> 00:32:34,172
Well, I mean...

569
00:32:34,172 --> 00:32:37,572
I came for a preliminary visit. But I left
my phone in the car, so I borrowed hers.

570
00:32:37,572 --> 00:32:38,638
Is that a problem?

571
00:32:38,638 --> 00:32:40,272
No, of course not.

572
00:32:40,272 --> 00:32:42,805
If you need to finish your call,
we'll go somewhere else...

573
00:32:42,805 --> 00:32:44,738
President!

574
00:32:49,638 --> 00:32:51,405
Then I'll take my leave.

575
00:32:51,405 --> 00:32:53,105
Ah, right.

576
00:32:58,272 --> 00:33:02,205
Your phone works perfectly fine,
so there's no excuse for not replying.

577
00:33:04,905 --> 00:33:07,205
Oh, and,

578
00:33:07,205 --> 00:33:09,838
answer calls from unknown numbers too.

579
00:33:10,672 --> 00:33:11,772
Let's go, Secretary Go.

580
00:33:11,772 --> 00:33:13,505
- Yes.
- Yes.

581
00:33:24,172 --> 00:33:25,372
- Well...
- Secretary Go.

582
00:33:25,372 --> 00:33:27,005
Yes.

583
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:28,772
Then, I'll get going.

584
00:33:37,972 --> 00:33:40,572
Wow.

585
00:33:40,572 --> 00:33:42,438
So that's why you were
desperately looking for her?

586
00:33:42,438 --> 00:33:43,905
And she's from the same company?

587
00:33:43,905 --> 00:33:45,405
Did you know?

588
00:33:45,405 --> 00:33:47,705
She's got a baby on the way,
and she wants to pretend it never happened?

589
00:33:47,705 --> 00:33:49,765
That's ridiculous.

590
00:33:49,765 --> 00:33:52,338
A baby? You're going to be a dad?

591
00:33:52,338 --> 00:33:53,438
It's not confirmed yet.

592
00:33:53,438 --> 00:33:54,738
What do you mean?

593
00:33:54,738 --> 00:33:56,038
Seriously, tell me.

594
00:33:56,038 --> 00:33:58,505
It's not really my decision to make.

595
00:33:58,505 --> 00:34:00,638
I've already prepared myself mentally.

596
00:34:00,638 --> 00:34:03,172
What? Explain it properly.

597
00:34:03,172 --> 00:34:05,305
I've been feeling kind of betrayed lately.

598
00:34:05,305 --> 00:34:07,305
Ugh, seriously.

599
00:34:10,905 --> 00:34:12,638
I misheard earlier, right?

600
00:34:12,638 --> 00:34:15,138
Marriage and a baby and all that?

601
00:34:15,138 --> 00:34:18,405
It's not certain yet, but you heard right.

602
00:34:19,903 --> 00:34:22,538
When... when did all this even happen?

603
00:34:22,538 --> 00:34:23,638
Marriage. A child.

604
00:34:23,638 --> 00:34:25,205
How come it happened so fast?

605
00:34:25,205 --> 00:34:29,138
And why didn't you tell me
about such happy news, huh?

606
00:34:29,138 --> 00:34:30,672
I'm really hurt by this.

607
00:34:30,672 --> 00:34:34,972
I'm not even sure you can call it good news.

608
00:34:34,972 --> 00:34:38,838
What is it? What are you so worried about?

609
00:34:38,838 --> 00:34:40,038
Why would I worry?

610
00:34:40,038 --> 00:34:42,572
We've known each other for years.

611
00:34:42,572 --> 00:34:46,172
That's the face you make
when you're really worried.

612
00:34:46,838 --> 00:34:51,105
Think of me as your bamboo forest
and say it all.

613
00:34:55,838 --> 00:34:57,765
I just know

614
00:34:57,765 --> 00:35:00,838
it's not my decision to make.

615
00:35:00,838 --> 00:35:03,205
If I were to become a real father,

616
00:35:03,205 --> 00:35:05,605
if I were to have a baby,

617
00:35:05,605 --> 00:35:08,605
I wonder if I could really
take proper responsibility.

618
00:35:08,605 --> 00:35:11,138
You were right.

619
00:35:11,138 --> 00:35:12,872
I guess I'm worried.

620
00:35:12,872 --> 00:35:15,105
Do you remember?

621
00:35:15,105 --> 00:35:19,905
My sister had nowhere to leave the kids.
She endured the pain until she collapsed.

622
00:35:19,905 --> 00:35:21,838
You offered to take care of them.

623
00:35:21,838 --> 00:35:25,872
Told her not to worry and go to the hospital.
It was chaos, remember?

624
00:35:25,872 --> 00:35:29,305
When she got back from the hospital,
the house was a complete mess.

625
00:35:29,305 --> 00:35:31,972
Both my nephews were hanging
off your broad back,

626
00:35:31,972 --> 00:35:34,072
and they refused to come down.

627
00:35:34,072 --> 00:35:36,638
I remember it was different
from raising Se Hyeon.

628
00:35:36,638 --> 00:35:39,172
Maybe because they were boys,
their energy is unreal.

629
00:35:39,172 --> 00:35:41,605
Ever since that day,
my back hurts when it rains.

630
00:35:41,605 --> 00:35:44,105
You know what I thought watching that?

631
00:35:44,105 --> 00:35:46,605
What? 'Kang Du Jun really can do anything.'
Something like that?

632
00:35:46,605 --> 00:35:49,105
Yes, the Kang Du Jun I know

633
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:52,272
is someone who keeps his word no matter what.

634
00:35:52,272 --> 00:35:54,238
So don't start worrying already.

635
00:35:54,238 --> 00:35:55,705
You'll do great, okay?

636
00:35:55,705 --> 00:35:57,605
As a dad,

637
00:35:57,605 --> 00:35:59,305
and as a husband...

638
00:36:01,407 --> 00:36:02,885
Jeez.

639
00:36:03,538 --> 00:36:05,672
You're being unusually serious.

640
00:36:05,672 --> 00:36:07,538
You're really putting on a whole show.

641
00:36:07,538 --> 00:36:09,272
Ugh, just go already.

642
00:36:09,272 --> 00:36:10,272
Well.

643
00:36:10,272 --> 00:36:12,238
Do the dishes before you leave.

644
00:36:12,938 --> 00:36:15,705
You are such an annoying type.

645
00:36:18,372 --> 00:36:19,738
What? The president?

646
00:36:19,738 --> 00:36:20,772
Whoa, no way.

647
00:36:20,772 --> 00:36:22,272
Hey, isn't that a total jackpot?

648
00:36:22,272 --> 00:36:23,705
Jackpot? What are you talking about?

649
00:36:23,705 --> 00:36:25,272
He completely fooled me.

650
00:36:25,272 --> 00:36:27,838
How many women must he have charmed
while hiding his identity?

651
00:36:27,838 --> 00:36:31,238
Well, with that face, women
probably didn't leave him alone.

652
00:36:31,238 --> 00:36:32,938
It's true.

653
00:36:34,738 --> 00:36:36,197
But

654
00:36:36,197 --> 00:36:38,038
don't you have something to tell me?

655
00:36:38,038 --> 00:36:39,772
What do you mean?

656
00:36:42,538 --> 00:36:45,472
Should I act like I know it or what?

657
00:36:46,238 --> 00:36:47,938
Well...

658
00:36:48,838 --> 00:36:50,772
Like... the guy you've been seeing lately.

659
00:36:50,772 --> 00:36:53,472
Huh? What did you say?

660
00:36:53,472 --> 00:36:55,172
That Min...

661
00:36:55,938 --> 00:36:57,905
No, never mind. It's nothing.

662
00:36:57,905 --> 00:37:00,205
What are you talking about?

663
00:37:01,072 --> 00:37:02,852
What about you,

664
00:37:02,852 --> 00:37:04,738
have you decided?

665
00:37:08,638 --> 00:37:10,938
Looking at your face, I guess not.

666
00:37:12,538 --> 00:37:15,072
Mi Ran, I actually got accepted
to study in Germany?

667
00:37:15,072 --> 00:37:16,238
Really?

668
00:37:16,238 --> 00:37:18,272
Hey, what's there to think about?
The answer is clear.

669
00:37:18,272 --> 00:37:19,738
Right? That's the right choice, right?

670
00:37:19,738 --> 00:37:21,705
Right, and honestly,

671
00:37:21,705 --> 00:37:23,838
haven't you sacrificed
everything for that company?

672
00:37:23,838 --> 00:37:25,938
Overtime, weekend work...

673
00:37:25,938 --> 00:37:28,105
You're still young. Go study abroad.

674
00:37:28,105 --> 00:37:31,205
Go study abroad first,

675
00:37:31,205 --> 00:37:34,305
and then think about the baby later.

676
00:37:36,072 --> 00:37:38,005
[Mom's Birthday]

677
00:37:41,772 --> 00:37:43,505
I'm here.

678
00:37:44,738 --> 00:37:46,705
Do they still celebrate your birthday
at school these days?

679
00:37:46,705 --> 00:37:48,872
You probably already blew out the candles.

680
00:37:49,672 --> 00:37:54,738
Even the department doesn't care.
Who would celebrate a part-time lecturer?

681
00:37:54,738 --> 00:37:58,372
Still, in the past, you used to
get cake and letters.

682
00:37:58,372 --> 00:38:00,238
You take it and eat it.

683
00:38:01,505 --> 00:38:04,205
Throw it away or give it to someone,
do whatever you want.

684
00:38:04,205 --> 00:38:06,538
I don't want to do things
I don't want to either.

685
00:38:17,105 --> 00:38:19,538
It was your choice.

686
00:38:19,538 --> 00:38:24,105
Whether it was a marriage forced by me
or whatever, it was your choice.

687
00:38:24,905 --> 00:38:26,338
What are you trying to say?

688
00:38:26,338 --> 00:38:28,272
I'm just curious.

689
00:38:28,272 --> 00:38:32,205
Curious why I was so hated
for something that wasn't my fault.

690
00:38:32,938 --> 00:38:34,438
If you regret it that much,

691
00:38:34,438 --> 00:38:36,272
you shouldn't have had me.

692
00:38:36,272 --> 00:38:38,805
Why give birth to me
and suffer your whole life? Why?

693
00:38:38,805 --> 00:38:40,372
Yes, you know it well.

694
00:38:40,372 --> 00:38:43,372
Giving birth to you was
a mistake from the start.

695
00:38:43,372 --> 00:38:46,938
My life has been a mess
ever since then. Satisfied?

696
00:38:48,138 --> 00:38:49,349
What?

697
00:38:49,349 --> 00:38:51,838
Did you want me to say it wasn't?

698
00:38:54,572 --> 00:38:59,472
Why bring up old stuff just to hurt me?

699
00:39:01,705 --> 00:39:03,605
Is this why you came?

700
00:39:03,605 --> 00:39:05,938
Just to upset me?

701
00:39:11,405 --> 00:39:13,405
I'm pregnant.

702
00:39:16,338 --> 00:39:19,105
That's why I came today.

703
00:39:19,105 --> 00:39:21,172
Because you're still my mom.

704
00:39:23,572 --> 00:39:25,538
Are you out of your mind?

705
00:39:25,538 --> 00:39:27,538
Not even married, and you are pregnant?

706
00:39:27,538 --> 00:39:28,538
Why would you say it like that?

707
00:39:28,538 --> 00:39:29,605
If you're going to
get rid of it anyway, hurry up.

708
00:39:29,605 --> 00:39:31,172
- Mom!
- Then what are you going to do?

709
00:39:31,172 --> 00:39:33,438
Are you going to keep it?

710
00:39:33,438 --> 00:39:35,605
Just a little while ago,

711
00:39:35,605 --> 00:39:39,138
weren't you the one making
a huge fuss about studying abroad?

712
00:39:39,138 --> 00:39:40,805
A choice?

713
00:39:40,805 --> 00:39:43,172
You're going to walk the same path as me?

714
00:39:44,138 --> 00:39:45,872
Do you really think

715
00:39:46,505 --> 00:39:48,453
you won't be reminded
of everything you gave up

716
00:39:48,453 --> 00:39:50,738
every time you look at that child?

717
00:39:51,505 --> 00:39:53,772
Are you sure you won't regret it?

718
00:39:58,172 --> 00:40:00,838
Do you think you'll be any different from me?

719
00:40:17,445 --> 00:40:22,238
I want ice cream.

720
00:40:26,038 --> 00:40:29,038
- Mom...
- Don't cry.

721
00:40:34,079 --> 00:40:36,773
- Come on.
- Mom.

722
00:40:36,773 --> 00:40:39,472
- I want that!
- Be careful.

723
00:40:39,472 --> 00:40:42,272
Let's ride a little more.

724
00:40:42,272 --> 00:40:45,038
Mom.

725
00:40:46,138 --> 00:40:48,572
Mom.

726
00:40:50,463 --> 00:40:54,085
Mom...

727
00:41:04,038 --> 00:41:08,705
[Obstetrics and Gynecology]

728
00:41:22,072 --> 00:41:24,805
You were diagnosed with
an endometrioma a few years ago.

729
00:41:24,805 --> 00:41:27,538
You clearly said pregnancy
would be difficult then.

730
00:41:27,538 --> 00:41:29,538
It was indeed a difficult situation.

731
00:41:29,538 --> 00:41:32,572
But seeing the yolk sac
perfectly settled in the womb,

732
00:41:32,572 --> 00:41:34,638
this is truly a miracle.

733
00:41:35,505 --> 00:41:38,005
Still, if you overexert or get stressed,

734
00:41:38,005 --> 00:41:40,705
you risk miscarriage
so you must be extra careful.

735
00:41:40,705 --> 00:41:43,205
If something happens to this baby,

736
00:41:43,205 --> 00:41:46,072
there may never be another chance.

737
00:41:46,805 --> 00:41:48,005
Young mom,

738
00:41:48,005 --> 00:41:51,338
don't be too scared.

739
00:41:54,038 --> 00:41:55,838
Mom?

740
00:42:04,472 --> 00:42:08,572
Mom, I'm scared.

741
00:42:08,572 --> 00:42:10,572
If you're scared, sleep with the light on.

742
00:42:10,572 --> 00:42:12,205
When will you sleep?

743
00:42:12,205 --> 00:42:14,172
I'll sleep when it's time, Hui Won.

744
00:42:14,172 --> 00:42:16,038
You're old enough to sleep alone now.

745
00:42:16,038 --> 00:42:18,505
Mom.

746
00:42:19,338 --> 00:42:22,605
How long will you keep calling for me?

747
00:42:22,605 --> 00:42:25,172
If it weren't for you, I...

748
00:42:25,172 --> 00:42:27,238
If it weren't for you, I...

749
00:42:31,672 --> 00:42:33,538
I'm going inside later, so sleep first.

750
00:42:33,538 --> 00:42:35,738
I'll come in after I drink this.

751
00:42:38,738 --> 00:42:42,738
[Airplane Ticket]

752
00:42:46,705 --> 00:42:51,472
If you're worried, shall I give you
a miscarriage prevention shot?

753
00:42:53,805 --> 00:42:55,572
I...

754
00:43:03,272 --> 00:43:07,005
I want to get rid of it.

755
00:43:19,005 --> 00:43:21,205
You seem confused right now.

756
00:43:21,205 --> 00:43:25,705
You don't have to decide today,
so take a few days to think.

757
00:43:39,505 --> 00:43:41,238
Hui Won.

758
00:43:42,938 --> 00:43:46,538
I brought some side dishes,
but you didn't answer...

759
00:43:55,038 --> 00:43:56,972
Is something wrong?

760
00:44:54,305 --> 00:44:56,272
Enjoy your meal.

761
00:44:56,272 --> 00:44:58,138
What? Pregnant?

762
00:45:01,505 --> 00:45:03,905
Hey, are you okay?

763
00:45:03,905 --> 00:45:05,305
You said he was a stranger.

764
00:45:05,305 --> 00:45:06,472
Then does that punk know?

765
00:45:06,472 --> 00:45:09,538
Forget it, give me his number.
I'll deal with this scoundrel.

766
00:45:09,538 --> 00:45:11,872
Ugh, stop it. What can you do?

767
00:45:11,872 --> 00:45:12,972
What do you mean?

768
00:45:12,972 --> 00:45:15,672
I should grab his collar
and demand responsibility.

769
00:45:15,672 --> 00:45:19,172
I'm not a kid anymore.
What responsibility are you talking about?

770
00:45:19,172 --> 00:45:21,138
I chose it anyway.

771
00:45:21,138 --> 00:45:22,205
You chose?

772
00:45:22,205 --> 00:45:24,872
What? Am I not allowed to?

773
00:45:24,872 --> 00:45:26,725
Are you

774
00:45:26,725 --> 00:45:28,438
really the Jang Hui Won I know?

775
00:45:28,438 --> 00:45:29,638
And what about you?

776
00:45:29,638 --> 00:45:31,305
I know everything too.

777
00:45:31,305 --> 00:45:33,372
About you and Mi Ran.

778
00:45:34,738 --> 00:45:37,238
I saw it, by chance.

779
00:45:37,238 --> 00:45:39,405
Hey, wait.

780
00:45:39,405 --> 00:45:40,872
Saw what?

781
00:45:40,872 --> 00:45:42,205
You two are dating.

782
00:45:42,205 --> 00:45:46,372
How could you do this without telling me?

783
00:45:46,372 --> 00:45:48,305
That's not it.

784
00:45:49,338 --> 00:45:51,872
I'm not dating Mi Ran.

785
00:45:53,138 --> 00:45:55,738
But I even saw you kissing.

786
00:45:55,738 --> 00:45:57,438
What?

787
00:45:58,972 --> 00:46:01,438
Wow, it's Cha Min Uk!

788
00:46:01,438 --> 00:46:03,405
- Hey, Cha Min Uk!
- Careful!

789
00:46:03,405 --> 00:46:05,905
Did you drink again?

790
00:46:05,905 --> 00:46:07,205
Yeah, team dinner.

791
00:46:07,205 --> 00:46:08,738
Ugh, you reek of alcohol.

792
00:46:08,738 --> 00:46:12,905
But I ditched the dinner to come see you.

793
00:46:12,905 --> 00:46:14,005
I did good, right?

794
00:46:14,005 --> 00:46:16,772
Good job. Get inside and rest now.

795
00:46:16,772 --> 00:46:18,072
Oh, right, this.

796
00:46:18,072 --> 00:46:20,505
You said you've been
craving my rolled omelet.

797
00:46:20,505 --> 00:46:22,338
- Yeah.
- I added flying fish roe.

798
00:46:22,338 --> 00:46:23,405
Make sure to eat it later.

799
00:46:23,405 --> 00:46:24,838
Ah, I love it.

800
00:46:24,838 --> 00:46:28,105
Ah, I love it! Cha Min Uk, you're the best!

801
00:46:29,472 --> 00:46:31,238
Hey, Hwang Mi Ran!

802
00:46:33,272 --> 00:46:35,005
Do you

803
00:46:35,672 --> 00:46:37,738
want to go out with me?

804
00:46:37,738 --> 00:46:39,538
- What?
- I'm asking you out.

805
00:46:39,538 --> 00:46:41,572
I like you.

806
00:46:51,505 --> 00:46:54,172
So you rejected her.

807
00:46:54,172 --> 00:46:56,605
I didn't even know.

808
00:46:57,305 --> 00:46:59,372
Enough about that.

809
00:47:00,405 --> 00:47:02,172
What will you do now?

810
00:47:02,172 --> 00:47:04,338
You're not actually going
to keep it, are you?

811
00:47:08,972 --> 00:47:10,938
Are you even thinking
about marrying that guy?

812
00:47:10,938 --> 00:47:14,172
No, it's not like that.

813
00:47:14,172 --> 00:47:15,538
You always said

814
00:47:15,538 --> 00:47:17,405
you didn't want to end up like your mom.

815
00:47:17,405 --> 00:47:20,972
I don't want you
to make a choice you'll regret.

816
00:47:22,005 --> 00:47:23,672
I know.

817
00:47:23,672 --> 00:47:26,138
But I just need

818
00:47:26,138 --> 00:47:28,738
a little more time to think.

819
00:47:32,638 --> 00:47:34,605
Ah, what?

820
00:47:38,238 --> 00:47:41,205
Call me if it gets hard. Even at dawn.

821
00:47:41,205 --> 00:47:43,038
Got it.

822
00:47:48,238 --> 00:47:50,272
Here.

823
00:47:50,272 --> 00:47:51,972
Thank you.

824
00:47:55,272 --> 00:47:57,705
Go.

825
00:47:57,705 --> 00:47:59,605
Hurry.

826
00:48:01,572 --> 00:48:04,105
- I'll leave.
- Go.

827
00:48:21,272 --> 00:48:22,272
Do you like that man?

828
00:48:22,272 --> 00:48:25,005
Oh, my! You scared me!

829
00:48:25,005 --> 00:48:27,572
But how did you find my place?

830
00:48:27,572 --> 00:48:29,572
Are you two dating?

831
00:48:29,572 --> 00:48:31,905
No, it's not like that.

832
00:48:31,905 --> 00:48:34,172
I just thought you two
looked all lovey-dovey.

833
00:48:34,172 --> 00:48:37,538
Seriously, we're just friends.

834
00:48:37,538 --> 00:48:39,272
Hey.

835
00:48:40,005 --> 00:48:41,605
No, President.

836
00:48:41,605 --> 00:48:44,738
How could you lie to me perfectly?

837
00:48:44,738 --> 00:48:46,605
What exactly did I lie about?

838
00:48:46,605 --> 00:48:50,805
Please pretend you don't know me at work.

839
00:48:52,105 --> 00:48:54,038
Fine.

840
00:48:54,038 --> 00:48:56,472
- What?
- I'll do as you wish.

841
00:48:56,472 --> 00:48:58,338
But,

842
00:48:58,338 --> 00:49:01,905
whoever your heart belongs to,
it's none of my business.

843
00:49:01,905 --> 00:49:05,572
But I do expect us both
to take responsibility for our actions.

844
00:49:22,772 --> 00:49:24,505
Does that make sense?

845
00:49:25,405 --> 00:49:27,538
Jang Hui Won is pregnant?

846
00:49:29,372 --> 00:49:31,805
[3 years ago]
This is our new employee, Cha Min Uk.

847
00:49:31,805 --> 00:49:34,838
Let's all give him a round of applause.

848
00:49:37,472 --> 00:49:42,372
Hello, I'm Cha Min Uk
starting today in the sales team.

849
00:49:42,372 --> 00:49:44,172
I look forward to working with you.

850
00:49:46,038 --> 00:49:47,905
Your desk is over there. Go take a seat.

851
00:49:47,905 --> 00:49:49,638
Yes.

852
00:49:49,638 --> 00:49:50,885
Hello.

853
00:49:54,138 --> 00:49:56,105
- Fighting!
- Fighting!

854
00:49:57,772 --> 00:50:00,305
So how was your first day?

855
00:50:00,305 --> 00:50:03,538
Wow, it was so hectic and nerve-wracking.

856
00:50:03,538 --> 00:50:05,838
I didn't even know whether food
was going into my mouth or my nose.

857
00:50:05,838 --> 00:50:08,838
If it weren't for the chocolate you gave me,
I would've been in big trouble.

858
00:50:08,838 --> 00:50:10,038
That stuff is expensive.

859
00:50:10,038 --> 00:50:12,438
I gave it to you because it's you.

860
00:50:12,438 --> 00:50:14,072
But our connection is really something.

861
00:50:14,072 --> 00:50:15,905
Middle school, high school, college,

862
00:50:15,905 --> 00:50:17,472
and now we work at the same company?

863
00:50:17,472 --> 00:50:19,138
Why? I like it.

864
00:50:19,138 --> 00:50:22,538
Weren't we supposed to
stick together forever?

865
00:50:22,538 --> 00:50:24,338
Huh?

866
00:50:24,338 --> 00:50:26,705
My treat today!

867
00:50:26,705 --> 00:50:28,305
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

868
00:50:28,305 --> 00:50:30,505
- Bottoms up!
- Bottoms up!

869
00:50:32,767 --> 00:50:34,898
Ah.

870
00:51:06,305 --> 00:51:08,772
But you guys left early yesterday.

871
00:51:08,772 --> 00:51:10,005
What time did you get home yesterday?

872
00:51:10,005 --> 00:51:12,138
[You've received 2,000,000 won
from Taehan Liquor Bonus.]

873
00:51:12,138 --> 00:51:13,138
Whoa, what's this?

874
00:51:13,138 --> 00:51:14,138
What is it?

875
00:51:14,138 --> 00:51:15,138
[You've received 2,000,000 won
from Taehan Liquor Bonus.]

876
00:51:15,138 --> 00:51:16,172
[You've received 1,500,000 won
from Taehan Liquor Bonus.]

877
00:51:16,172 --> 00:51:17,172
[To celebrate New President's inauguration]
Bonus?

878
00:51:17,172 --> 00:51:18,272
The new president gave it to us.

879
00:51:18,272 --> 00:51:19,872
- Really?
- Yeah.

880
00:51:19,872 --> 00:51:20,905
Seriously?

881
00:51:20,905 --> 00:51:22,005
[To celebrate New President's inauguration]
It's a bonus.

882
00:51:22,005 --> 00:51:24,272
- A bonus!
- From the new president?

883
00:51:24,272 --> 00:51:26,472
Huh? Here's President.

884
00:51:50,972 --> 00:51:53,905
- He's handsome.
- So cool.

885
00:51:53,905 --> 00:51:57,405
Wow, he has such presence.

886
00:51:57,405 --> 00:51:59,605
Isn't he basically a model?

887
00:51:59,605 --> 00:52:01,338
You're mine.

888
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:09,072
Oh, President! Welcome to Taehan Liquor.

889
00:52:14,705 --> 00:52:16,738
Thank you for the welcome.

890
00:52:16,738 --> 00:52:18,538
Ah, yes.

891
00:52:40,505 --> 00:52:42,072
The door closes.

892
00:52:42,072 --> 00:52:44,005
Hold on!

893
00:52:48,438 --> 00:52:49,705
Are you getting on?

894
00:52:49,705 --> 00:52:51,338
Ah, I...

895
00:52:51,338 --> 00:52:54,138
I'll take the next one.

896
00:52:54,138 --> 00:52:55,938
Alright.

897
00:52:56,972 --> 00:52:59,138
The door closes.

898
00:53:07,005 --> 00:53:08,705
Unbelievable.

899
00:53:11,038 --> 00:53:12,038
Assistant Manager, you saw him, right?

900
00:53:12,038 --> 00:53:13,372
Yeah, totally my type.

901
00:53:13,372 --> 00:53:14,705
Even as a guy, I think he's impressive.

902
00:53:14,705 --> 00:53:16,405
The bonus was such a pleasant surprise.

903
00:53:16,405 --> 00:53:19,738
Right? He's young but so thoughtful.

904
00:53:19,738 --> 00:53:21,572
And those shoulders...

905
00:53:21,572 --> 00:53:24,105
His shoulders are so broad,
you could surf on them.

906
00:53:24,105 --> 00:53:26,105
Assistant Manager Choi, did you break up?

907
00:53:27,238 --> 00:53:30,438
Why? Can't I say he's my type?

908
00:53:31,572 --> 00:53:33,738
Pfft, greedy much?

909
00:53:34,505 --> 00:53:35,972
But Manager Jang,

910
00:53:35,972 --> 00:53:39,672
don't you feel any urge to pursue
someone like our new president?

911
00:53:39,672 --> 00:53:42,905
Whoever your heart belongs to,
it's none of my business.

912
00:53:42,905 --> 00:53:45,605
But I do expect us both
to take responsibility for our actions.

913
00:53:45,605 --> 00:53:48,338
Ugh, how annoying.

914
00:53:50,038 --> 00:53:51,505
Hey, why is everyone like this with me?

915
00:53:51,505 --> 00:53:53,372
Ugh, how annoying.

916
00:53:53,372 --> 00:53:55,838
Hey, Kim Tak Soo! Get over here!

917
00:53:55,838 --> 00:53:57,305
Tak Soo!

918
00:53:57,305 --> 00:53:59,772
Fine, I'll let it slide this once.

919
00:54:08,671 --> 00:54:10,847
[Taehan]

920
00:54:22,238 --> 00:54:24,605
- I'll get your beer ready.
- Oh.

921
00:54:24,605 --> 00:54:26,021
[Yellow]

922
00:54:34,533 --> 00:54:37,638
This isn't Try Beer.

923
00:54:37,638 --> 00:54:39,038
No wonder it tasted...

924
00:54:39,038 --> 00:54:41,872
Oh, dear...

925
00:55:03,972 --> 00:55:06,302
We are planning to launch a new beer product

926
00:55:06,302 --> 00:55:08,838
for the global market
within a short timeframe.

927
00:55:08,838 --> 00:55:12,505
We are aiming to target
the global market soon

928
00:55:12,505 --> 00:55:15,872
with plans to launch a new beer product.

929
00:55:15,872 --> 00:55:17,938
Could you give me more specific plans?

930
00:55:17,938 --> 00:55:21,505
First, we plan to research
each country's beer market.

931
00:55:21,505 --> 00:55:26,105
Based on the results, we plan
to go full-scale product development phase.

932
00:55:26,105 --> 00:55:29,472
How many people do you think
will participate in

933
00:55:29,472 --> 00:55:32,405
today's market research in Japan?

934
00:55:33,738 --> 00:55:35,138
This is the cold storage facility,

935
00:55:35,138 --> 00:55:36,805
where proven-quality beer

936
00:55:36,805 --> 00:55:39,938
is packaged into cans or kegs and stored.

937
00:55:39,938 --> 00:55:42,538
It seems fairly well organized.

938
00:55:44,172 --> 00:55:45,905
Secretary Go.

939
00:55:50,905 --> 00:55:54,105
This place is totally disorganized.
Get it sorted out quickly.

940
00:55:55,872 --> 00:55:58,772
This is the brew house where we
make wort, the main beer ingredient.

941
00:55:58,772 --> 00:56:03,072
Since beer production involves yeast,
please pay special attention to hygiene.

942
00:56:03,072 --> 00:56:04,772
Understood.

943
00:56:07,738 --> 00:56:10,672
Oh! Wait, hold on!

944
00:56:22,738 --> 00:56:24,005
Which floor are you going to?

945
00:56:24,005 --> 00:56:26,005
Ah, I'm going to 15...

946
00:56:26,005 --> 00:56:27,838
15th floor.

947
00:56:42,538 --> 00:56:44,672
Oh, let me carry them for you.

948
00:56:44,672 --> 00:56:46,938
- I'm fine.
- With those thin wrists of yours,

949
00:56:46,938 --> 00:56:49,638
what if they snap
while you're carrying those?

950
00:56:51,072 --> 00:56:53,372
Give them to me.

951
00:56:55,605 --> 00:56:57,305
It's heavy.

952
00:57:03,272 --> 00:57:05,738
Yeah, what?

953
00:57:05,738 --> 00:57:08,772
Are you crazy? What if you mess that up?

954
00:57:08,772 --> 00:57:10,172
Don't even think about leaving work today.

955
00:57:10,172 --> 00:57:13,705
Fix it now and email it
to me. Get it together!

956
00:57:17,672 --> 00:57:21,445
I'll get off here.

957
00:57:21,445 --> 00:57:25,477
- Take care.
- Then, I'll get going.

958
00:57:31,205 --> 00:57:34,305
Huh? Wait, don't you need these?

959
00:57:34,305 --> 00:57:36,738
You should take them with you.

960
00:57:37,572 --> 00:57:41,038
For the first half of next year,
we're exploring a plan

961
00:57:41,038 --> 00:57:45,505
to develop a new product by reducing
the calories of our existing Try beer.

962
00:57:45,505 --> 00:57:46,738
We're also considering
seasonal promotional items.

963
00:57:46,738 --> 00:57:48,372
- Did you get dragged here?
- For that,

964
00:57:48,372 --> 00:57:49,738
- Lighten up a little.
- we plan to collaborate with other brands.

965
00:57:49,738 --> 00:57:54,372
We'll showcase collaborative products
with various brands to customers.

966
00:57:54,372 --> 00:57:57,305
That concludes the briefing.

967
00:57:58,305 --> 00:58:00,538
Call me if it gets hard. Even at dawn.

968
00:58:00,538 --> 00:58:02,272
Got it.

969
00:58:09,272 --> 00:58:12,172
Thank you for your hard work
preparing the presentation.

970
00:58:12,905 --> 00:58:15,505
- Not at all.
- Everyone received bonuses last time, right?

971
00:58:15,505 --> 00:58:17,405
Ah, we were extremely grateful.

972
00:58:17,405 --> 00:58:19,438
We were all completely surprised.

973
00:58:19,438 --> 00:58:22,472
Right? President, you are the best.

974
00:58:25,072 --> 00:58:28,305
Then you should earn your pay.

975
00:58:28,305 --> 00:58:30,505
I'm not saying work harder
because you got bonuses.

976
00:58:30,505 --> 00:58:34,038
But you should at least work
to the level of your salaries.

977
00:58:34,038 --> 00:58:38,072
If there's anything lacking...

978
00:58:39,705 --> 00:58:40,705
Everything.

979
00:58:40,705 --> 00:58:44,605
The annual 3-year new product design report
due every September is inadequate.

980
00:58:44,605 --> 00:58:47,038
By now, winter promotions
should be finalized as a baseline.

981
00:58:47,038 --> 00:58:49,938
Next half-year's product proposals
should've been ready too.

982
00:58:49,938 --> 00:58:51,305
Based solely on today's briefing,

983
00:58:51,305 --> 00:58:53,872
there are zero concrete cases.

984
00:58:56,738 --> 00:58:58,872
Since it's our first meeting together,

985
00:58:58,872 --> 00:59:01,238
please provide more
detailed enhancements moving forward.

986
00:59:01,238 --> 00:59:04,405
Yes, we'll fix this.

987
00:59:05,438 --> 00:59:06,905
Ah, one more thing.

988
00:59:06,905 --> 00:59:10,972
Is the Germany program selectee
in this New Product Development Team?

989
00:59:10,972 --> 00:59:12,105
Yes.

990
00:59:12,105 --> 00:59:15,205
Our team's Manager Jang Hui Won was chosen.

991
00:59:16,638 --> 00:59:18,805
Ah, I see.

992
00:59:18,805 --> 00:59:20,505
Manager Jang Hui Won.

993
00:59:21,838 --> 00:59:22,972
Yes?

994
00:59:22,972 --> 00:59:25,505
Do you actually intend to go to Germany?

995
00:59:25,505 --> 00:59:28,605
I know there are plenty of responsibilities
here requiring your attention.

996
00:59:28,605 --> 00:59:30,738
Wouldn't it be overwhelming?

997
00:59:39,013 --> 00:59:40,405
Jeez.

998
00:59:40,405 --> 00:59:42,338
His personality is something else.

999
00:59:42,338 --> 00:59:44,505
But why is he treating
Manager Jang like that?

1000
00:59:44,505 --> 00:59:47,472
Exactly. Manager Jang
really wants to go to Germany.

1001
00:59:47,472 --> 00:59:49,472
Right, Manager Jang?

1002
00:59:55,272 --> 00:59:57,205
You told me not to act like
I know you at work.

1003
00:59:57,205 --> 00:59:58,572
People might misunderstand.

1004
00:59:58,572 --> 01:00:01,938
I knew you were annoying,
but this is downright shameless.

1005
01:00:01,938 --> 01:00:04,038
Why would you ask that there?

1006
01:00:04,038 --> 01:00:05,372
Because I'm curious.

1007
01:00:05,372 --> 01:00:07,705
I have no idea what you think.

1008
01:00:07,705 --> 01:00:09,205
Since we're on the subject, let me ask.

1009
01:00:09,205 --> 01:00:10,805
Are you going to keep the baby?

1010
01:00:10,805 --> 01:00:12,738
I haven't decided yet.

1011
01:00:12,738 --> 01:00:16,605
Even if I do, I won't marry you.

1012
01:00:19,138 --> 01:00:21,605
You said it doesn't matter who I like.

1013
01:00:21,605 --> 01:00:25,638
Plus, it's a waste of time discussing this
with someone who views marriage as business.

1014
01:00:25,638 --> 01:00:28,105
And I'll never have a loveless marriage.

1015
01:00:28,105 --> 01:00:30,705
Let's just stop all of this here.

1016
01:00:32,072 --> 01:00:33,338
You're bold even without alcohol.

1017
01:00:33,338 --> 01:00:34,338
What did you say?

1018
01:00:34,338 --> 01:00:35,738
You said before, didn't you?

1019
01:00:35,738 --> 01:00:38,472
That it's your own business
and you'll take responsibility.

1020
01:00:38,472 --> 01:00:40,205
But...

1021
01:00:41,672 --> 01:00:44,105
Now that I know about it,

1022
01:00:44,105 --> 01:00:47,672
this is my business too.

1023
01:00:47,672 --> 01:00:51,572
So let's meet at least three times a week.

1024
01:00:51,572 --> 01:00:55,238
- What?
- Love. Let's give it a try properly.

1025
01:01:34,138 --> 01:01:35,972
Let's just say we both enjoyed it.

1026
01:01:35,972 --> 01:01:37,172
- Keep it cool.
- Cool?

1027
01:01:37,172 --> 01:01:39,672
I let it slide that she was with another man,
and this is how she treats me?

1028
01:01:39,672 --> 01:01:41,638
Either treat her well
or torment her. Pick one.

1029
01:01:41,638 --> 01:01:43,072
You're not seeking revenge, are you?

1030
01:01:43,072 --> 01:01:45,005
How did you feel about
the father of Hui Won's child?

1031
01:01:45,005 --> 01:01:46,872
Are you here to ask about that now?

1032
01:01:46,872 --> 01:01:48,272
Then what about taking it slow?

1033
01:01:48,272 --> 01:01:49,305
I don't want to stop.

1034
01:01:49,305 --> 01:01:51,372
The secret woman,
Kang Du Jun's illegitimate child.

1035
01:01:51,372 --> 01:01:53,072
We just need to frame it, right?

1036
01:01:53,072 --> 01:01:57,503
Because of you, our entire team
is about to be investigated.

1037
01:01:57,503 --> 01:01:58,938
Ow.

1038
01:01:58,938 --> 01:02:01,605
President, we've got a serious problem.
